Phaeophyta) forming a fringing zone in the Falkland Islands.
Giant kelp plants were sampled along a transect in the austral
autumn (May 1986) and late spring (December 1986) which,
according to previous frond weight analysis, were the times when
extremes in population parameters were expected. Plant density
and holdfast wet weights were similar for both seasons, but
plants had more fronds and the fronds weighed more in spring
than in autumn. Consequently, in autumn the frond biomass (1{\textperiodcentered}1
