after the commissioning of the extended ocean outfall. The
abundance and recruitment of adult and juvenile kelp plants,
Ecklonia radiata were also investigated. At the outfall and
control locations counts were made for a total of three periods,
one before and two after the commissioning of the outfall. Within
each period kelp abundance was determined on three random
