elsewhere, either in adjacent seagrass beds or on reefs hundreds
of metres to kilometres away. There was a disproportionate
retention of drift kelp Ecklonia radiata by H. erythrogramma .
Based on these results, we propose that spatial subsidies in the
form of drift macroalgae result in a weak influence of H.
erythrogramma on attached macroalgae},
