double sigma coordinate model was applied as a diagnostic tool
to calculate features of ocean circulation off the coast of
Western Europe, particularly in the area between La Chapelle
Bank and Porcupine Bank. Calculations derived from the model
indicated density-driven poleward currents continuous from the
Portuguese to the Irish shelves in accordance with actual
observations and numerical results available. The model also
indicates that seasonal winds strongly modify flow over the
shelf and upper slope.},
