distributed biomass ( Callitriche platycarpa and Ranunculus
penicillatus). 6. These results indicate that aquatic plants with
an emergent strategy are able to take better advantage of zones
with reduced hydraulic forces than submerged plants.
Additionally, this plant occurrence will be determined by the
relationship between total plant drag and root strength.
