diagnoses by a-CGH with the average new diagnosis rate of 11.8{\%}
(range 5.4-28.8{\%}). Barriers to implementation of the process and
outcome data collection and analysis were significant and related
to time pressures, lack of personnel or staff to support this
activity, and competing quality improvement initiatives at the
institutional home of some genetics centers.},
