document that present-day populations of E. radiata have adjusted
their gametophyte thermal sensitivity according to their local
environment, and further indicate that these differences are
adaptive rather than phenotypic. Collectively, these findings
suggest that the scope for thermal adaptation and gametophyte
performance of E. radiata across most of its Australian
