is needed for study of seasonal change, to identify functional
roles of associated fauna and to monitor potential coral spawning
events. Benthic landers and seafloor observatories have great
potential in these areas. Only with a better understanding of the
natural variability of the cold-water coral environment can
informed decisions about the environmental sensitivity of
cold-water coral reefs and their management be made.},
