oceanographic regimes, with the Chile region showing longshore
coherency over much smaller spatial scales ({\~{}}60 km) than on the
coast of WNA ({\~{}}140 km). Through a spatial analysis of coastal
orientation I suggest that the characteristic length scales may
be traced to the geomorphologic character of the ocean margins.
The second chapter examines spatial patterns of primary
production through long-term means of coastal chlorophyll-a
