variability related to the North Atlantic Oscillation. The
extremely rapid surface warming in the enclosed and
semi-enclosed European and East Asian Seas surrounded by major
industrial/population agglomerations may have resulted from the
observed terrestrial warming directly affecting the adjacent
coastal seas. Regions of freshwater influence in the European
and East Asian Seas seem to play a special role in modulating
and exacerbating global warming effects on the regional scale.},
