significant aspects of physical processes in the coastal zones
of the Great Lakes. The review is based on examples ranging from
lake-wide experiments like the International Field Year on the
Great Lakes (IFYGL) to several process-oriented coastal boundary
layer experiments. The basic circulations in the nearshore zone
and coastal boundary layer are summarized. The review concludes
with suggestions for future work on the understanding of the
physical processes that would have a bearing on lake management
in the coastal zones of the Great Lakes.},
