of algal drift were made to aid in assessing the potential
importance of benthic algae as a dispersal mechanism. Algal
clumps often rolled in a manner similar to that of terrestrial
tumbleweeds; mark-recapture work showed that algal clumps can
move up to 0.5 km/day and that algal drift is a frequent
