benthic fauna, including mobile shrimps and fishes; dispersal
was more efficient over sand than over seagrass. Dispersal of
fauna via this mobile habitat should entail lower risk than
other adult dispersal stratagems such as vertical migration or
rafting; this mechanism would be most advantageous for brooding
species or those with limited planktonic phases. Differential
fidelity to clumps tumbling across seagrass versus sand suggests
that the algae could facilitate exchange of fauna between
isolated seagrass patches.},
