. g. extremes vs. average). Our$\backslash$nfindings argue for a more rigorous quantitative view of scale in$\backslash$nthe study of marine dispersal processes, where relative terms such$\backslash$nas 'short' and 'long', 'open' and 'closed', 'retained' and 'exported'$\backslash$nare defined only in conjunction with explicit definitions of the$\backslash$nscale and process of interest. This shift in perspective represents$\backslash$nan important step towards unifying theoretical and empirical studies$\backslash$nof dispersal processes in marine and terrestrial systems.},
